# Block Events (FULL GUIDE)

## Step 1: Where This Goes

Create a NEW class:

BlockListener.java

## Step 2: Class Structure

```java
public class BlockListener implements Listener {

    @EventHandler
    public void onBlockBreak(BlockBreakEvent event) {
        Block block = event.getBlock();

        if (block.getType() == Material.DIAMOND_BLOCK) {
            event.setDropItems(false);
            block.getWorld().dropItemNaturally(block.getLocation(), new ItemStack(Material.EMERALD, 2));
        }
    }
}
```

## Step 3: Breakdown

@EventHandler
→ tells Spigot this is an event

BlockBreakEvent
→ runs when block breaks

if (block.getType() == Material.DIAMOND_BLOCK)
→ checks block type

setDropItems(false)
→ stops normal drops

dropItemNaturally(...)
→ spawns custom items

## Step 4: IMPORTANT

You MUST register this in main class:

getServer().getPluginManager().registerEvents(new BlockListener(), this);

## Step 5: What Happens

Breaking diamond block → gives emeralds instead

## Step 6: Common Mistakes

❌ Forgetting to register event
→ NOTHING happens

